What These Results Mean

random_device: The slow speed is normal and expected on Windows when pulling from BCryptGenRandom in a tight loop. 
The OS rate-limits to prevent entropy pool exhaustion. Passing PractRand cleanly confirms it is delivering true high-
entropy output.

csprng: 0.52 GB/s is very strong for a cryptographic generator. 
  For comparison:
    AES-CTR (hardware accelerated) often hits 2–6 GB/s
    Pure-software ChaCha20 implementations typically range 0.3–1.0 GB/s
    This implementation is in the upper tier for software-only ChaCha20. Clean PractRand pass = cryptographically sound.

fast_RNG: 10.7 GB/s with zero anomalies in 2 GB; excellent for non-cryptographic PRNGs.
  wyrand (its direct inspiration) claims ~10–12 GB/s
  This variant matches that while passing the same rigorous tests.
